  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Feature Issue\n\nCurrently, cases when wrong card is tapped at attempt to long, sign transaction, change PIN and other flows are not consistent and can cause bugs.\n\n### User Story\n\nAs a user, I want to see nice error if I'm using wrong card and want to be able to continue working with app after tapping valid keycard.\n\n### Description\n### Case 1: Wrong card on login or on send transaction flow\nEndless \"Processing\", can continue if tap valid  card which corresponds multiaccount\n\n### Case 2: Wrong card during account creation \\ pairing\nTried wrong card on stage of back up seed phrase (so last stage) , after tapping invalid card got\nendless \"Processing\", can't proceed with valid card even after restarting application (endless Processing)\nLogs: [Status-debug-logs-10.zip](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/4753171/Status-debug-logs-10.zip)\n**No workaround in this case**\n\n### Case 3: Wrong card on changing PIN or on adding new account in wallet\n![ezgif com-video-to-gif (21)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/84161828-fd8a1c00-aa6f-11ea-9a6d-36e54084cff1.gif)\nAfter tapping wrong card\n- can't enter right pin\n- if close this screen and open \"Send transaction\" screen - still can't enter PIN code.\n**Workaround:** go back to \"Change passcode\" and finish the process with valid card\n\n\n#### Acceptance criteria\nIn all cases can see error, can close it, tap valid card and proceed",
